  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WASH emergency aid for conflict-affected women, girls, men and boys in DeZ</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Oxfam will implement Water Sanitation and Hygiene (WASH) interventions to reach most vulnerable populations. Outputs and key activities are mentioned below: Output 1  - 27,650 people in need have improved access to adequate and safe water supply The main activities under this output are: &#x2022; Supply and installation of household (HH) water tanks for the 850 most vulnerable HHs. &#x2022; Light emergency repairs including operating and maintenance materials (spot rehabilitation) &#x2022; Technical assessment, design and monitoring  Output 2  - 59,500 vulnerable people receive hygiene messages and are equipped with hygiene materials   The main activities under this output are: &#x2022; Risk assessment and community dialogue &#x2022; Distribution of hygiene kits and regular replenishment to needy population &#x2022; Hygiene promotion  - Covid -19 &amp; WASH activities on improved hygiene practices    &#x2022; Tracking beneficiary perceptions on Covid -19 through the Community Perception Tracker    Output 3  - 59,500 people in need have improved access to adequate sanitation and solid waste management (SWM)  The main activities under this output are: &#x2022; Cleaning and repair of sewers &#x2022; Supply and installation of waste containers at municipal level  In addition to the above key activities that directly contribute to results, Oxfam will implement the following activities to ensure the quality, monitoring and sustainability of the project: &#x2022; Start -up, inception workshop and community consultation &#x2022; Baseline and Endline Survey &#x2022; Risk assessment and protection training for Safe Programming and Safeguarding &#x2022; Supply of Covid19 protective equipment for staff and volunteers  &#x2022; Workshops to find alternative solutions for water resource management.  &#x2022; Accountability and feedback system (including Post Distribution Monitoring (PDMs) and survey CTO)</narrative>
  </description>
